race.comment: The G1 Futurity Stakes and star mare TREASURETHE MOMENT (7) is the one to beat. She was electric winning the G1 Memsie over this route first up last time in, sitting off a fast pace and charging away. Her prep derailed a bit after that but she was in front inside the 100m in a Cox Plate just two runs back. She's the best horse in the race and black odds seem fair. PERICLES (1) is the danger. His first up run last time in for the new yard was very good winning the G2 Tramway, close up in top races thereafter. He'll track the speed and take beating. EVAPORATE (3) resumes. He's a consistent horse who was third to Jimmysstar in the Orr here before a break. In the mix. FEROCE (6) tested Tom Kitten all the way first up in the G3 Kevin Heffernan over this route. That race fitness can play a big role. VEIGHT (4) has been rock solid in two runs back and has claims.
